{"title": "Short Nonfiction Collection, Vol. 100", "description": "Volume 100 of the Short Nonfiction Collection celebrates 16 years (2007-2023) of volunteer readings which reflect the wide range of nonfiction writing. Volume 100 exemplifies this diversity with topics as far afield as declassified CIA documents and Bible verses (CIA Avian Training; Story of Creation; Mark Twain on Biblical Patriarchs; Hidden Years at Nazareth). Other selections highlight the natural world and scientific inquiry (White Hurricane; Ancient Meadows; Improving Natural Knowledge; Know the $100 Note); as well as the complexities of human morals, love, politics, and behavior (American Genius; Frauds on the Bank of Liverpool; Wreck of a Slave Ship; Louisa Catherine Johnson to John Quincy Adams; Seven Pillars of Wisdom; and the Hippocratic Oath). Inventions and crafts are treated in Steel Railway Rails; and The Willow Pattern. Lastly, humor is not neglected (Reflections on Riding; and The Two Husbands). Summary by Sue Anderson\r\n", "duration": 17033, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18", "name": " Various"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/snf100_2310_librivox/snf100_2310.jpg", "genres": ["*Non-fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Sue Anderson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Sue Anderson"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Ancient Meadows", "readers": [7389], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/snf100_2310_librivox/snf100_ancientmeadows_cornish_scc_64kb.mp3", "duration": 957}, {"section": 2, "title": "CIA  Avian Training Program, 1973-1974", "readers": [3003], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/snf100_2310_librivox/snf100_aviantraining_cia_sa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 698}, {"section": 3, "title": "Forgiveness: Mark Twain On The Biblical Patriarchs Joseph And Esau", "readers": [6454], "path": "https://www.archive.o